cs.RO, cs.PL, cs.SE, cs.MS, cs.SY 

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper is focused on geometric relations between rigid bodies targeted to robotic applications. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely as the paper presents a DSL for geometric relations. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is another possible category as the paper discusses the development of tools for editing and checking semantic constraints. 
- cs.MS (Mathematical Software) is a possible category as the paper deals with coordinate representations and constraints. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also a possible category as the paper is focused on rigid-body coordinate representations and their standardization.
